 ُ َﮫﻘَﻣَر ﱠﺪَﺳ
To subsist; to afford to feed oneself or someone; to keep someone on one’s 
feet; to afford the bare necessities of life; to help someone to stay alive or 
alleviate hunger; hand-to-mouth existence. 
